# plugin-developer engagement

**New repos are created PRIVATE.** Casa installs plugins from private repos
(the in-container `GITHUB_TOKEN` authenticates the clone), so private is
sufficient for the user's own agents — and Claude Code hard-blocks creating a
*public* repo from within an engagement regardless. Converge on the plugin
design + name in `superpowers:brainstorming` (step 1) before creating the repo;
use the default name `casa-plugin-<slug>` unless the user asked otherwise.
Making a plugin public later (to *share* it) is a deliberate step the user runs
themselves: `gh repo edit <repo> --visibility public`.

